  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An alchemist knows how to transmute matter, body and spirit through the foundations of alchemy, through which the four basic elements - water, air, fire and earth - can be manipulated into the four basic acts of alchemical practice: Calcinatio, Putrefatio, Distillatio and Sublimatio.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">At 17th level you finally complete the alchemical study with the red phase, Rubedo, with which you can perform four acts simultaneously. As a bonus action on your turn, you may perform one of the four described below. Each of them creates a simple mixture that can be used by anyone as an action:</span></p><ul><li>@UUID[Compendium.world.profession-features.PDX24RuzBqZuMGLv]{Calcinatio (Rubedo, 4 acts)}</li><li>@UUID[Compendium.world.profession-features.LGwobeWyYMJHQbOX]{Putrefatio (Rubedo, 4 acts)}</li><li>@UUID[Compendium.world.profession-features.KfZZCizPrLWYAcs7]{Distillatio (Rubedo, 4 acts)}</li><li>@UUID[Compendium.world.profession-features.daz2MA5hgfMsGZoG]{Sublimatio (Rubedo, 4 acts)}</li></ul><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can execute these procedures as many times as shown in the table. At the end of a short or long rest, existing mixtures lose their power and you recover all uses. With experience, alchemists will learn how to quickly use multiple procedures in the same shift, combining the four fundamental effects to obtain new and mysterious results. <br style=\"font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;orphans:2;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\" /></span></p>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
